Initialize a new Git repository "git init"
Clone a repository "git clone <url>"
Check current status "git status"
Track a new file "git add <file>"
Track all changes "git add ."
Unstage a file "git reset <file>"
Commit staged changes "git commit -m 'message'"
Amend the last commit "git commit --amend"
View commit history "git log"
View a one-line commit log "git log --oneline"
See changes in working directory "git diff"
See staged changes "git diff --cached"
Create a new branch "git branch <name>"
Switch branches "git checkout <name>"
Create and switch branches "git checkout -b <name>"
Merge a branch into current "git merge <branch>"
Delete a branch "git branch -d <name>"
Check remote URLs "git remote -v"
Add a remote repository "git remote add origin <url>"
Push to remote (first time) "git push -u origin <branch>"
Push changes to remote "git push"
Pull latest changes "git pull"
Fetch changes without merging "git fetch"
Revert a file to last commit "git checkout -- <file>"
Show who changed what line "git blame <file>"
Stash changes "git stash"
Apply last stash "git stash pop"
List all stashes "git stash list"
Remove all stashes "git stash clear"
Undo last commit but keep changes "git reset --soft HEAD~1"
Hard reset to previous commit "git reset --hard HEAD~1"

